<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,457,908,934]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description</emphasis>
. Living specimens in squeeze-preparation ~ 
<number box="[990,1036,908,934]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="470.0">470</number>
µm long and ~ 
<number box="[1228,1272,908,934]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="135.0">135</number>
µm wide (
<figureCitation box="[343,433,948,974]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[403,433,948,974]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Anterior and posterior ends rounded. Epidermis completely ciliated. Large rhabdoid glands in longitudinal rows (
<figureCitation box="[783,867,988,1014]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[837,867,988,1014]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Body colorless in transmitted light. Frontal glands well developed, extend from frontal pore posteriorly to level behind statocyst. Mouth opening on ventral surface, middle of body. Digestive central syncytium extends from position behind statocyst posteriorly to level of seminal bursa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Ovary unpaired, extends from level of mouth posteriorly to seminal bursa (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1294,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 
<number box="[1266,1294,1148,1174]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[264,294,1188,1214]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
A). Testes paired, follicular; extend from frontal glands posteriorly to seminal vesicle (
<figureCitation box="[273,370,1228,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 
<number box="[339,370,1228,1254]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Single gonopore present; opens directly to male copulatory organ. Unclear from histological sections whether gonopore also opens to seminal bursa (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1151,1308,1334]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="23.[264,367,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,542,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[264,1323,542,1722]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 14. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; A. Sagittal histological section of posterior end of body. B, C. Projections of whole-mount stained with Alexa- 488 - labeled phalloidin and viewed with confocal microscopy. B. Ventral view of posterior portion of specimen. C. Ventral view of bursal nozzle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174301/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[1122,1151,1308,1334]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
A)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Seminal bursa a dense syncytial mass surrounding sperm and bursal nozzle (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1296,1348,1374]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 
<number box="[1266,1296,1348,1374]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[264,294,1388,1414]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
A). Bursa capped anteriorly with several cells that separate bursa from developing eggs (
<figureCitation box="[273,360,1428,1454]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="23.[264,367,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,542,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[264,1323,542,1722]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 14. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; A. Sagittal histological section of posterior end of body. B, C. Projections of whole-mount stained with Alexa- 488 - labeled phalloidin and viewed with confocal microscopy. B. Ventral view of posterior portion of specimen. C. Ventral view of bursal nozzle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174301/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[330,360,1428,1454]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Bursal nozzle S-shaped; composed of many (~ 
<number box="[966,996,1428,1454]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="17.0">17</number>
) disjunct, actin-rich nozzle components, through which sperm pass on way to ovary (
<figureCitation box="[940,1036,1468,1494]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 
<number box="[1006,1036,1468,1494]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[1069,1097,1468,1494]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
A–C)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Isodiametrid-type male copulatory organ composed of a muscular penis (~ 
<number box="[1170,1199,1508,1534]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
µm long) invaginated into a muscular seminal vesicle (
<figureCitation box="[812,912,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[274,1322,434,1503]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[274,1333,434,1503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; photomicrographs of a living specimen. A. Dorsal view of squeezed specimen. B. Dorsal view of copulatory organs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174300/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 
<number box="[882,912,1548,1574]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[949,978,1548,1574]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
A, B). Space within seminal vesicle filled with sperm that surrounds penis (
<figureCitation box="[812,897,1588,1614]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="23.[264,367,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,542,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[264,1323,542,1722]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 14. Archaphanostoma marcusi sp. nov.; A. Sagittal histological section of posterior end of body. B, C. Projections of whole-mount stained with Alexa- 488 - labeled phalloidin and viewed with confocal microscopy. B. Ventral view of posterior portion of specimen. C. Ventral view of bursal nozzle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174301/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[867,897,1588,1614]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1628,1654]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was very fast moving and fairly uncommon in our samples. Due to a lack of available specimens, only a single mature animal was fixed for histological sectioning. Unfortunately, this single specimen is slightly damaged around the gonopore, and as such, it is not possible to determine whether it is solely a male gonopore, or a common gonopore that also opens to the seminal bursa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1323,547,1894]" lastBlockId="22.[264,1322,284,390]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Our species is placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[754,968,1828,1853]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" genus="Archaphanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,968,1828,1853]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Archaphanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its possession of the diagnostic character—a syncytial seminal bursa. 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1001,1868,1893]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" genus="Archaphanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="species" species="marcusi">
<emphasis box="[869,1001,1868,1893]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">A. marcusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs most substantially from the other three known species of the genus by its possession of a bursal nozzle. A disjunct nozzle is an uncommon occurrence among members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1245,324,350]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="family">Isodiametridae</taxonomicName>
, but is present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hooge and Tyler, 2003" authorityName="Hooge and Tyler" authorityYear="2003" box="[386,919,364,390]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" genus="Aphanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="species" species="bruscai">
<emphasis box="[386,643,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Aphanostoma bruscai</emphasis>
Hooge and Tyler, 
<number box="[860,919,364,390]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrov" box="[1035,1247,364,390]" pageId="22" pageNumber="50" refString="Petrov, A., Hooge, M., &amp; Tyler, S. (2006) Comparative morphology of the bursal nozzles in Acoels (Acoela, Acoelomorpha). Journal of Morphology, 267, 634 - 648." type="journal article" year="2006">
Petrov et al. 
<number box="[1183,1247,364,390]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
